All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Administrator
    This class will be used to store administrator information and will have access to methods that will allow them to add or remove courses from the catalog
    AdministratorController
    This class controls and manages a list of administrator users on the system
    AdminMenuPanel
    The Panel for the Admin Menu which allows the admin to select what operations they would like to do for the courses
    BrowseCatalogPanel
    The Panel for viewing all of the course catalog which will display all courses in the catalog
    ClientCommunicationController
    This class is primarily used to communicate with the server via sockets
    ClientGUIController
    This class is used to communicate between the GUI and the ClientCommunicationController
    Course
    This class represents a course a student can enroll in or an administrator can modify
    CourseController
    This class manages everything to do with courses
    CourseOffering
    This class represents a section or offering of a specific course
    CourseOfferingController
    This class manages everything to do with course offerings
    CourseTest
    Test Class for Unit Testing all components of Class Course
    DatabaseController
    This class manages our database, including loading and saving data on students and courses
    LoginSelectPanel
    The Login Selection Panel which allows the user to selection which type of login they would like to do
    MainView
    The Frame of the GUI which has all the panels and is able to switch between them on the frame
    Registration
    This class represents a registration for a course between a course offering and a student; it also tracks a student's grade in the course
    RegistrationAppClient
    This class is meant to be the main application class for the client side of the client server application
    RegistrationAppServer
    This class is meant to be run to start the server side of the client server of the registration application
    RegistrationController
    This class manages everything to do with registrations
    ServerCommunicationController
    This class is primarily used to communicate with clients and handle multi-threading tasks
    Session
    This class implements the runnable interface so that user can interact with the application during runtime.
    Student
    This class represents a student
    StudentController
    This class manages everything to do with students
    StudentMenuPanel
    The Panel for the Student Menu which allows the student to select what operations they would like to do for their courses
    StudentTest
    Test Class for Unit Testing all components of Class Student
